# repositories/
#
# Why this folder exists:
# Repositories are the only layer that talks to the database (via Knex).
# They contain raw SQL / query builder calls and return plain JavaScript objects.
# This isolates DB concerns — if you ever switch from MySQL to PostgreSQL,
# only this folder changes.
#
# Naming convention: <module>.repository.js
# Example: user.repository.js, project.repository.js
